flawed_nl_solution:
There are 3 * 5 = <<3*5=15>>15 tadpoles.
Two-thirds of the tadpoles will survive to become frogs, so 2 * 15 / 3 = <<2*15/3=10>>10 tadpoles will grow into frogs.
When the tadpoles grow up, there will be 5 + 10 = <<5+10=51>>51 frogs in the pond.
The pond can only sustain 8 frogs, so 51 - 8 = <<51-8=43>>43 frogs will need to find a new pond.
#### 43

error_details.explanation: The result of this computation should be 15, not 51. It appears two adjacent digits were swapped.
